The key insight is that `e ∈ ∅` is definitionally `False` (via `Set.mem_empty_iff_false : a ∈ (∅ : Set α) ↔ False` which is `Iff.rfl`), so we can use `.elim` on membership proofs.

```lean
def matchingIndepMatroid (G : Graph α β) : IndepMatroid α where
  E := V(G)
  Indep := fun S ↦ ∃ M, G.IsMatching M ∧ S ⊆ V(G, M)
  indep_empty := by
    refine ⟨∅, ⟨Set.empty_subset _, fun {_} {_} h => h.elim⟩, Set.empty_subset _⟩
```
